{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"96fbf15c-36e4-4e41-acec-4f9f3dba3308","content":"The workspace is empty, so I'll answer from .NET MAUI knowledge:\n\n**1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — ✅ Correct for .NET 10. This is the iOS platform-specific attached property that insets your page content to respect the safe area. You'll need the namespace:\n\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\n**2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` on a Grid** — ⚠️ This is **not** a standard public .NET MAUI property. Your tutorial may be outdated or referencing a Xamarin.Forms-era API.\n\n### Recommended approach for a full-bleed background image:\n\nInstead of `IgnoreSafeArea`, use a layered layout — don't set `UseSafeArea` on the page itself, and manually pad your content:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\">\n    <Grid>\n        <!-- Background fills entire screen including behind notch -->\n        <Image Source=\"bg.png\" Aspect=\"AspectFill\" />\n\n        <!-- Content respects safe area via padding -->\n        <Grid Padding=\"{OnPlatform iOS='20,44,20,34'}\"\n              VerticalOptions=\"Fill\">\n            <!-- Your UI here -->\n        </Grid>\n    </Grid>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nOr, use `UseSafeArea` on the page and place the background image in a parent layout that isn't affected (e.g., set it as the `Window.Page` background or use `Page.BackgroundImageSource`).\n\n**TL;DR:** `UseSafeArea` is correct; `IgnoreSafeArea` on a Grid is not a valid .NET MAUI API — restructure your layout instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bfb63799-e9ab-4526-b563-1fac9237724b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - there's no codebase here. The user is asking a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI safe area APIs. Let me answer based on my knowledge.